### 🔷 1. Why 2025 Was a REAL Inflection Point (Not Hype)

Three independent trends converged simultaneously — this is called **Convergent Validation**:

**① Capability Breakthroughs**
- At **ICPC World Finals 2025** (Baku), OpenAI achieved a **perfect score — all 12 problems solved** in 5 hours, beating 139 human university teams
- Google DeepMind's Gemini 2.5 solved **10/12 (gold-medal level)**
- Problem C was solved by AI but by **none of the 139 human teams**
- **GDPval Benchmark**: Claude Opus 4.1 → **49% win rate** vs human expert programmers; GPT-5 → **40.6%** (18 months earlier: below 15%)
- Dario Amodei (Anthropic CEO): AI will write **90% of code** within months
- Sundar Pichai (Google CEO): AI tools increased developer productivity by **10%** = equivalent to adding **8,000 full-time developers** overnight

**② Mainstream Adoption**
- Stack Overflow 2025: **84% of professional developers** use or plan to use AI coding tools; **51% daily use**
- DORA 2025 Report: **90% enterprise adoption** (up 14% YoY); **2 hours/day median usage**; quality maintained or improved

**③ Enterprise Productization**
- **25%** of Y Combinator Winter 2025 startups use AI-generated code as primary development approach; some report **95% of codebase written by AI**
- **Workday acquired Sana for $1.1 billion** — buying AI agents as core product architecture
- GitHub, Microsoft, JetBrains all redesigned platforms for AI-native workflows

> 🔑 Key: Evidence came from **academia + independent surveys + startup economics + financial decisions** — not from vendor marketing.

