### 🔷 5. The Director's 4 Responsibilities (General Agent Role)

1. **Set the Intent** — describe the goal clearly
2. **Provide Access** — give the agent access to your files/repo (the "dossier")
3. **Review the Work** — evaluate what the agent builds
4. **Course Correct** — give feedback; agent adapts

---

### 🔷 6. The 5-Phase Evolution Arc

| Phase | What Happens |
|---|---|
| **1. Incubation** | Use General Agent to explore vague requirements (Week 1–2) |
| **2. Crystallization** | Extract learnings into clear specifications (Week 3) |
| **3. Specialization** | Build Custom Agent using SDK (Week 4–5) |
| **4. Production** | Specialist runs at scale — fast, cheap, reliable (Week 6+) |
| **5. Continued Evolution** | General Agent improves Specialist & builds the next one (Ongoing) |

---

### 🔷 7. The 3 Anti-Patterns to Avoid (Exam Favourite!)

| Anti-Pattern | What It Means | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| **Premature Specialization** | Building Custom Agent before requirements are clear | Stay in incubation longer |
| **Perpetual Incubation** | Using General Agents for high-volume production | Evolve to specialization |
| **Skipping Incubation** | Specifying Custom Agent without exploring first | Always incubate first |

