### 🔷 8. Skills Needed for AI-Native Development

Traditional CS teaches: syntax mastery, algorithm optimization, manual debugging

AI-Native requires:
- **Specification writing** — clear specs determine AI output quality
- **Prompting & collaboration** — directing AI requires precision about intent
- **Agent design** — orchestrating systems, not writing code
- **System thinking** — how components interact matters more than implementation
- **Validation & testing** — you evaluate AI output as quality control

